00:23:28.880 --> 00:23:30.350 align:middle line:84%
>>FLANAGAN: Yeah,
well, telomeres

00:23:30.350 --> 00:23:36.750 align:middle line:84%
are little-- they're on the
ends of our chromosomes.

00:23:36.750 --> 00:23:42.590 align:middle line:84%
And telomeres are
little-- they're

00:23:42.590 --> 00:23:47.110 align:middle line:84%
made up of-- let's
see, what is it?

00:23:47.110 --> 00:23:47.610 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:23:47.610 --> 00:23:50.520 align:middle line:90%


00:23:50.520 --> 00:23:53.160 align:middle line:90%
Right now it's escaping me.

00:23:53.160 --> 00:23:59.580 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, they're little things
on the end of our cells, and--

00:23:59.580 --> 00:24:01.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Like little
hairs or projectiles?

00:24:01.490 --> 00:24:05.440 align:middle line:84%
>>FLANAGAN: Little projectiles
on the ends of our cells.

00:24:05.440 --> 00:24:13.010 align:middle line:84%
And they're actually
made up of DNA codes.

00:24:13.010 --> 00:24:18.690 align:middle line:84%
And basically, when our
cells divide, they break off.

00:24:18.690 --> 00:24:24.530 align:middle line:84%
And every time they break
off, it prevents the cells

00:24:24.530 --> 00:24:26.560 align:middle line:90%
from dividing that many times.

00:24:26.560 --> 00:24:30.970 align:middle line:84%
And so over time,
generally a lifetime,

00:24:30.970 --> 00:24:33.700 align:middle line:84%
your cells can only
divide about 50 times.

00:24:33.700 --> 00:24:36.810 align:middle line:84%
And then they stop dividing
and goes into senescence,

00:24:36.810 --> 00:24:38.380 align:middle line:90%
and we die.

00:24:38.380 --> 00:24:42.670 align:middle line:84%
And basically, the
holy grail of medicine

00:24:42.670 --> 00:24:45.900 align:middle line:84%
is looking for telomerase,
which is an enzyme that

00:24:45.900 --> 00:24:48.810 align:middle line:84%
restores the link
of the telomeres

00:24:48.810 --> 00:24:51.820 align:middle line:84%
so that your cells
can divide forever.

00:24:51.820 --> 00:24:56.000 align:middle line:90%
And so that's the holy grail.

00:24:56.000 --> 00:25:00.440 align:middle line:84%
And basically I've discovered
the holy grail of medicine.

00:25:00.440 --> 00:25:02.550 align:middle line:84%
And there's a lot of
work on telomeres.

00:25:02.550 --> 00:25:07.120 align:middle line:84%
They've discovered herbs
from China and various kinds

00:25:07.120 --> 00:25:11.250 align:middle line:84%
of things that increase
the length of telomeres.

00:25:11.250 --> 00:25:14.780 align:middle line:90%
But basically, I've done it.

00:25:14.780 --> 00:25:18.630 align:middle line:90%
And we can restore that.

00:25:18.630 --> 00:25:22.340 align:middle line:84%
And theoretically our cells
