00:48:53.749 --> 00:48:55.040 align:middle line:90%
to be seeing you in a few days.

00:48:55.040 --> 00:48:57.060 align:middle line:84%
And I called you up
and said, can you

00:48:57.060 --> 00:48:59.510 align:middle line:84%
tell me in one simple
sentence, what is electricity?

00:48:59.510 --> 00:49:02.820 align:middle line:84%
Because that's something
that obviously is not well

00:49:02.820 --> 00:49:05.620 align:middle line:84%
understood in the
academic circles just yet.

00:49:05.620 --> 00:49:08.060 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise we wouldn't be
living in this crude way.

00:49:08.060 --> 00:49:11.120 align:middle line:84%
And you said, if I
can remember exactly,

00:49:11.120 --> 00:49:15.780 align:middle line:84%
you said, electricity is the
flow of electrons from a higher

00:49:15.780 --> 00:49:19.270 align:middle line:90%
potential to a lower potential.

00:49:19.270 --> 00:49:20.320 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: Yeah.

00:49:20.320 --> 00:49:22.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, that
has to interface

00:49:22.930 --> 00:49:25.740 align:middle line:84%
with the subject of light,
which has to interface

00:49:25.740 --> 00:49:30.710 align:middle line:84%
with the subject of a
multi-dimensional universe,

00:49:30.710 --> 00:49:31.210 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:49:31.210 --> 00:49:32.250 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: Yes.

00:49:32.250 --> 00:49:35.340 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So we're talking about
what is condensed as the light

00:49:35.340 --> 00:49:37.970 align:middle line:84%
here, maybe information
systems that

00:49:37.970 --> 00:49:40.380 align:middle line:84%
are being derived from
another dimensional field

00:49:40.380 --> 00:49:45.594 align:middle line:84%
even and somehow
directed, or how does--?

00:49:45.594 --> 00:49:53.040 align:middle line:84%
>>FLANAGAN: Well, the thing is
is everything is simplicity.

00:49:53.040 --> 00:49:56.320 align:middle line:84%
If it's too complicated,
it's not true.

00:49:56.320 --> 00:50:00.160 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we can get into higher
mathematical functions and all

00:50:00.160 --> 00:50:02.150 align:middle line:84%
these things, but
when it gets down

00:50:02.150 --> 00:50:10.450 align:middle line:84%
to the structure of the universe
and the way everything is

00:50:10.450 --> 00:50:12.420 align:middle line:90%
is simplicity itself.

00:50:12.420 --> 00:50:15.880 align:middle line:84%
Because if you can't boil
it down into something

00:50:15.880 --> 00:50:19.390 align:middle line:84%
where you can simply explain
it, then it's not true.

00:50:19.390 --> 00:50:21.260 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:50:21.260 --> 00:50:22.250 align:middle line:90%
Well said.

00:50:22.250 --> 00:50:25.130 align:middle line:84%
OK, so another thing I
think Keshe was saying

00:50:25.130 --> 00:50:27.250 align:middle line:84%
is that it's
possible we will all

00:50:27.250 --> 00:50:31.380 align:middle line:84%
be operating our own
little anti-gravity devices

00:50:31.380 --> 00:50:34.050 align:middle line:90%
as our transport, right?

00:50:34.050 --> 00:50:37.550 align:middle line:84%
I read about that
decades ago, that that

00:50:37.550 --> 00:50:39.230 align:middle line:90%
should've been the case by now.

00:50:39.230 --> 00:50:41.231 align:middle line:84%
So we're looking-- what
are you seeing down

00:50:41.231 --> 00:50:47.599 align:middle line:84%
the road through your
lens as to our future--

00:50:47.599 --> 00:50:48.640 align:middle line:90%
just that, our transport?

00:50:48.640 --> 00:50:50.190 align:middle line:84%
What kind of future
transport do we

00:50:50.190 --> 00:50:53.300 align:middle line:84%
have waiting for
us as individuals?

00:50:53.300 --> 00:50:54.875 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: Anti-grav cars.

00:50:54.875 --> 00:50:56.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Just like-- yeah.

00:50:56.000 --> 00:50:57.166 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: Floating around.

00:50:57.166 --> 00:51:00.070 align:middle line:90%


00:51:00.070 --> 00:51:02.235 align:middle line:90%
They won't bang into each other.

00:51:02.235 --> 00:51:04.380 align:middle line:90%
[BOTH LAUGH]

00:51:04.380 --> 00:51:06.990 align:middle line:84%
We'll be able to
transport ourselves

00:51:06.990 --> 00:51:09.086 align:middle line:90%
anywhere almost instantaneously.

00:51:09.086 --> 00:51:11.900 align:middle line:90%


00:51:11.900 --> 00:51:14.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Will they
programed by our thoughts?

00:51:14.170 --> 00:51:16.420 align:middle line:84%
I mean, do they work with
consciousness at that point?

00:51:16.420 --> 00:51:19.710 align:middle line:84%
Or do you still have to
put in a vector point?

00:51:19.710 --> 00:51:20.900 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: I'm not sure.

00:51:20.900 --> 00:51:24.280 align:middle line:84%
Pretty much I think it's
going to be a thought thing.

00:51:24.280 --> 00:51:27.090 align:middle line:90%
But not sure yet.

00:51:27.090 --> 00:51:29.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then once
they're using anti-gravity

00:51:29.810 --> 00:51:32.820 align:middle line:84%
for the purposes of
betterment of life

00:51:32.820 --> 00:51:34.320 align:middle line:84%
on the planet for
the people instead

00:51:34.320 --> 00:51:36.560 align:middle line:84%
of sequestered
black technologies,

00:51:36.560 --> 00:51:38.441 align:middle line:84%
then we're looking
at, like you say,

00:51:38.441 --> 00:51:40.440 align:middle line:84%
they won't bump into each
other, because they'll

00:51:40.440 --> 00:51:44.332 align:middle line:84%
have the whole understanding
of affinity and repulsion.

00:51:44.332 --> 00:51:46.290 align:middle line:84%
Nothing will ever have
to bump into each other.

00:51:46.290 --> 00:51:50.540 align:middle line:84%
We won't be bumping into
each other metaphorically,

00:51:50.540 --> 00:51:53.050 align:middle line:84%
hopefully on many
levels by then.

00:51:53.050 --> 00:51:54.216 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:51:54.216 --> 00:51:56.520 align:middle line:90%
[BOTH LAUGH]

00:51:56.520 --> 00:51:58.860 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about our
future power sources.

00:51:58.860 --> 00:52:00.480 align:middle line:84%
As Sterling was
saying, there are

00:52:00.480 --> 00:52:02.710 align:middle line:84%
many that are right
on the horizon,

00:52:02.710 --> 00:52:04.440 align:middle line:90%
cold fusion is already there.

00:52:04.440 --> 00:52:06.260 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's just
waiting to kind of drop

00:52:06.260 --> 00:52:10.910 align:middle line:84%
into the marketplace, Keshe's
technology, motor generators.

00:52:10.910 --> 00:52:14.400 align:middle line:84%
What do you see as some
of the kind of top runners

00:52:14.400 --> 00:52:17.150 align:middle line:90%
yourself for this?

00:52:17.150 --> 00:52:18.590 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: Wow.

00:52:18.590 --> 00:52:21.390 align:middle line:90%
I think Keshe is right on edge.

00:52:21.390 --> 00:52:27.310 align:middle line:84%
Keshe said that in December
he's going to deliver 10,000

00:52:27.310 --> 00:52:33.100 align:middle line:84%
5,000-watt plasma generators
to customers who have ordered

00:52:33.100 --> 00:52:33.750 align:middle line:90%
them.

00:52:33.750 --> 00:52:36.990 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that's
just right on the edge.

00:52:36.990 --> 00:52:41.770 align:middle line:84%
If that's true,
then it's happening.

00:52:41.770 --> 00:52:46.300 align:middle line:84%
And I mean that said, there
are multiple other people who

00:52:46.300 --> 00:52:48.650 align:middle line:84%
are working on these
things, who have

00:52:48.650 --> 00:52:51.000 align:middle line:84%
multiple other
technologies, everything

00:52:51.000 --> 00:52:56.480 align:middle line:84%
from magnetic motors
to electrostatic motors

00:52:56.480 --> 00:52:59.262 align:middle line:90%
and all kinds of--

00:52:59.262 --> 00:53:00.220 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Water motors.

00:53:00.220 --> 00:53:02.200 align:middle line:84%
>>FLANAGAN: Water motors
and things like that.

00:53:02.200 --> 00:53:07.030 align:middle line:84%
So that said, I think we're
right on the edge of all of it.

00:53:07.030 --> 00:53:10.960 align:middle line:90%
It's breaking loose right now.

00:53:10.960 --> 00:53:14.770 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So after
everything you've

00:53:14.770 --> 00:53:17.800 align:middle line:84%
been through in your lifetime
and everything going further

00:53:17.800 --> 00:53:22.960 align:middle line:84%
back into another lifetime that
your being has been through,

00:53:22.960 --> 00:53:25.680 align:middle line:84%
do you feel now that we're,
like you just said, we really,

00:53:25.680 --> 00:53:27.860 align:middle line:84%
truly are on the
cusp of breaking free

00:53:27.860 --> 00:53:30.322 align:middle line:84%
of these more tyrannical
types of systems?

00:53:30.322 --> 00:53:31.780 align:middle line:84%
Do you feel we're
going to make it,

00:53:31.780 --> 00:53:34.530 align:middle line:84%
we're going to hop
across that chasm?

00:53:34.530 --> 00:53:35.400 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: I do.

00:53:35.400 --> 00:53:38.439 align:middle line:84%
I think we're going
to make it for sure.

00:53:38.439 --> 00:53:40.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And I assume
you have more things

00:53:40.230 --> 00:53:43.290 align:middle line:84%
up your sleeve besides just
this one technology coming out

00:53:43.290 --> 00:53:44.345 align:middle line:90%
in six months?

00:53:44.345 --> 00:53:45.970 align:middle line:84%
OK, I'm not going to
press you on that.

00:53:45.970 --> 00:53:48.370 align:middle line:84%
How about if we do
a third show later

00:53:48.370 --> 00:53:51.000 align:middle line:84%
on when you start getting a
little closer to some of those

00:53:51.000 --> 00:53:53.160 align:middle line:84%
and when we start seeing
the first free energy

00:53:53.160 --> 00:53:55.830 align:middle line:90%
devices popping through?

00:53:55.830 --> 00:53:56.555 align:middle line:90%
How's that sound?

00:53:56.555 --> 00:53:57.180 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: OK.

00:53:57.180 --> 00:53:57.740 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:53:57.740 --> 00:54:01.300 align:middle line:84%
And then I also wanted
to ask you-- going back

00:54:01.300 --> 00:54:04.930 align:middle line:84%
in your own
reflections, what do you

00:54:04.930 --> 00:54:08.709 align:middle line:84%
think Tesla's
greatest legacy was?

00:54:08.709 --> 00:54:10.250 align:middle line:84%
Of all that he
brought to the planet,

00:54:10.250 --> 00:54:13.790 align:middle line:90%
what was his greatest legacy?

00:54:13.790 --> 00:54:15.980 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: Powering the world.

00:54:15.980 --> 00:54:22.280 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if it wasn't for Tesla,
we'd still be in the Stone Age.

00:54:22.280 --> 00:54:26.170 align:middle line:84%
He made it possible to have
power all over the world.

00:54:26.170 --> 00:54:29.720 align:middle line:84%
It's just that there are
greedy corporations that

00:54:29.720 --> 00:54:31.810 align:middle line:84%
are charging an arm
and a leg for it

00:54:31.810 --> 00:54:34.010 align:middle line:90%
and making us energy slaves.

00:54:34.010 --> 00:54:36.180 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, we don't
like those corporations.

00:54:36.180 --> 00:54:36.679 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:54:36.679 --> 00:54:38.570 align:middle line:84%
And we only have a
minute or so left.

00:54:38.570 --> 00:54:40.790 align:middle line:90%
And what about your own legacy?

00:54:40.790 --> 00:54:44.284 align:middle line:84%
What do you feel is now
and will be-- of course,

00:54:44.284 --> 00:54:46.450 align:middle line:84%
you don't know because
you're still inventing things

00:54:46.450 --> 00:54:47.533 align:middle line:90%
and have a long way to go.

00:54:47.533 --> 00:54:50.600 align:middle line:84%
But at this point, what
is your greatest legacy?

00:54:50.600 --> 00:54:51.384 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: Love.

00:54:51.384 --> 00:54:52.320 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:54:52.320 --> 00:54:53.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You know what?

00:54:53.320 --> 00:54:55.460 align:middle line:90%
I have to say this, Patrick.

00:54:55.460 --> 00:54:57.390 align:middle line:84%
Because when it
comes down to it,

00:54:57.390 --> 00:54:58.940 align:middle line:84%
that's the fabric
of the universe.

00:54:58.940 --> 00:55:02.560 align:middle line:84%
And I had to say, I think
that is a very true answer.

00:55:02.560 --> 00:55:04.230 align:middle line:90%
I watch you with people.

00:55:04.230 --> 00:55:06.770 align:middle line:84%
And one thing you do
is you treat people

00:55:06.770 --> 00:55:10.660 align:middle line:84%
with so much love
and so much respect.

00:55:10.660 --> 00:55:14.910 align:middle line:84%
I do believe that is your legacy
above and beyond anything else.

00:55:14.910 --> 00:55:18.290 align:middle line:84%
Because I mean really, doesn't
that power the whole enchilada?

00:55:18.290 --> 00:55:20.999 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: It does.

00:55:20.999 --> 00:55:21.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:55:21.540 --> 00:55:24.540 align:middle line:84%
Well, Patrick, thank you so much
for coming here and spending

00:55:24.540 --> 00:55:25.400 align:middle line:90%
the time with us.

00:55:25.400 --> 00:55:28.090 align:middle line:90%
>>FLANAGAN: So my pleasure.

00:55:28.090 --> 00:55:29.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It has
truly been an honor

00:55:29.930 --> 00:55:32.214 align:middle line:84%
to talk with Dr.
Patrick Flanagan today.

00:55:32.214 --> 00:55:34.380 align:middle line:84%
If you haven't watched our
first interview with him,

00:55:34.380 --> 00:55:36.870 align:middle line:84%
you'll want to check it
out on Gaiam TV archives.

00:55:36.870 --> 00:55:40.520 align:middle line:84%
Until next time, thank you for
joining us here on Gaiam TV.

